{"lemma":"عُرْسِ","slug":"عُرْسِ","root":"ع.ر.س","root_slug":"ع-ر-س","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ر-س","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n28643","n28644","n28645","n28646","n28647"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8F%D8%B1%D9%92%D8%B3%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"wedding, the occasion of concluding marriage; wedding-feast, marriage-feast"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"spouse; husband or wife","examples":[{"text":"عِرْسَانِ","english":"husband and wife"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of عَرُوس (ʕarūs)","tags":["form-of","plural"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Borrowed from Aramaic עַרְסָא / ܥܲܪܣܵܐ (ʕarsā, “bed, litter, luxurious couch etc.”), originally referring to the ceremonial presentation of a bride to her husband for marriage to be consumed. Doublet of عَرْش (ʕarš, “throne”), regular cognate to the Aramaic since Proto-Semitic s₂ gives Arabic š and Aramaic s. The vocalism of the present word, if not merely being owed to the reduced ă of the ḥaṭaf pataḥ in the absolute state, needs to represent an unattested dialectal Aramaic form, like Old Armenian կուղբ (kułb, “beaver”) is from ܟܲܠܒܵܐ (kalbā, “dog”)\n\nSecondarily formed to عَرُوس (ʕarūs) or its plural, itself the passive adjective to the above wedding term.\n\nSee the etymology of the corresponding lemma form."},"ipa":["/ʕurs/","/ʕirs/","/ʕu.rus/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n28643","headword_ar":"عَرْسٌ","root":"Ers","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A wall which is placed between the two"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"main lateral"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"walls of the winter-chamber, not reaching to the further end thereof,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"then the beam is laid from the inner extremity of that wall to the further end of the"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1999},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chamber,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and it is roofed over,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K, TA,) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the whole chamber is roofed over: what is between the two walls"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"above mentioned"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sahowap","text_ar":"سَهْوَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and what is beneath the beam"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with what is screened by the middle wall from the portion"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the chamber"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which is the entrance"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muixodaE","text_ar":"مُِخْدَع"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"this is done for the sake of more warmth, and only in cold countries:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and it is called in Pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"byjh","text_ar":"بيجه"},{"kind":"text","text":"[correctly"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"PyJh","text_ar":"پيچه"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaroSN","text_ar":"عَرْصٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is [said to be] a dial. var. thereof. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n28644","headword_ar":"عُرْسٌ","root":"Ers","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, S, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EurusN","text_ar":"عُرُسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, S, K) substs. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEorasa","text_ar":"اَعْرَسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as signifying “ he had his wife conducted to him on the occasion of his marriage, ” and “ he went in to her: ” (Az, TA:) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ceremony of conducting a bride to her husband:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ministration,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"performance, of a marriage, and of the ceremony of conducting the bride to her husband:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or [simply]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"marriage:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coitus:"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nikaAHN","text_ar":"نِكَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K, TA:) because this is the real thing intended by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_iEoraAs","text_ar":"الاـِعْرَاس"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) in the first of these senses, it is masc. and fem.; or, accord. to some, fem. only: as masc., its pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoraAsN","text_ar":"اَعْرَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and as fem., its pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EurusaAtN","text_ar":"عُرُسَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) Hence [the trad.],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_i*aA duEiYa A^aHadukumo A_ilaY waliymapi","text_ar":"اـِذَا دُعِىَ اَحَدُكُمْ اـِلَى وَلِيمَةِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EurosK faloyujibo","text_ar":"عُرْسٍ فَلْيُجِبْ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When any one of you is invited to a marriage-feast,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a feast given on the occasion of the conducting of a bride to her husband, let him consent."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) ―         -b2-  And hence, (Az, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A marriage-feast:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A 'Obeyd, Az, S, O, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a feast made on the occasion of conducting a bride to her husband:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) in this sense it is masc.: (Msb:) or mase, and fem.: (S, O:) or fem., and sometimes mase. (Az, TA.) A rájiz says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A_in~aA wajadonaA Eurusa AlHan~aATi\n                      \n                     \n                        lay^iymapF ma*omuwmapa AlHuw~aATi"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily we found the marriage-feast of the wheatseller to be mean, discommended for the managers:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuwaATapN","text_ar":"حُوَاطَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Az, S, O, TA.) Pl. as above, i. e.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoraAsN","text_ar":"اَعْرَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EurusaAtN","text_ar":"عُرُسَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, O, K.) [See an ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xurosN","text_ar":"خُرْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b3-  [And hence,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A state of rejoicing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IB, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA^otamN","text_ar":"مَاْتَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.) ―         -b4-  The dim. is ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EurayosN","text_ar":"عُرَيْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; which is extr., [accord. to those who hold it to be fem. only,] for [accord, to them] it should have"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", being a fem. n. of three letters. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Az","S","Msb","K","TA","O"]},{"entry_id":"n28645","headword_ar":"عِرْسٌ","root":"Ers","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A man's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wife:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, O, Msb, K:) and a woman's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"husband:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, Msb, K:) pl. (in both senses, TA)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoraAsN","text_ar":"اَعْرَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O, Msb, K, TA:) the dual,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EirosaAni","text_ar":"عِرْسَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", is sometimes applied to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"male and female,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"husband and wife:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a male and female ostrich:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IB:) and the sing., to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mate"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the lion: (S, A, O, K:) and the pl. is applied, metaphorically, by Málik Ibn-Khuweylid El-Hudhalee, to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lions."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aibonu EirosK","text_ar":"اِبْنُ عِرْسٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The weasel;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a weasel;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain small animal,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, S, O, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"resembling the rat"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfaA^orap","text_ar":"الفَاْرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"), (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"smaller than the cat,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, O, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having the lower lip cleft"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$otaru","text_ar":"اَشْتَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and very short ears, as though they were amputated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and having a canine tooth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"called in Persian"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAsuwo","text_ar":"رَاسُوْ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Mgh:) the name is determinate and indeterminate: (TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banaAtu EirosK","text_ar":"بَنَاتُ عِرْسٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) applied to the males and the females; (O, K;) like as you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aibonu A=waY","text_ar":"اِبْنُ ا=وَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aibonu maxaADK","text_ar":"اِبْنُ مَخَاضٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aibonu labuwnK","text_ar":"اِبْنُ لَبُونٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aibonu maA='K","text_ar":"اِبْنُ مَا=ءٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and in the pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banaAtu A=waY","text_ar":"بَنَاتُ ا=وَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banaAtu maxaADK","text_ar":"بَنَاتُ مَخَاضٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banaAtu labuwnK","text_ar":"بَنَاتُ لَبُونٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banaAtu maA='K","text_ar":"بَنَاتُ مَا=ءٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; or, accord. to Akh, you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banaAtu EirosK","text_ar":"بَنَاتُ عِرْسٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banuw EirosK","text_ar":"بَنُو عِرْسٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banaAtu naEo$K","text_ar":"بَنَاتُ نَعْشٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banuw naEo$K","text_ar":"بَنُو نَعْشٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, O.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","O","Msb","K","TA","IB","A","Lth"]},{"entry_id":"n28646","headword_ar":"عِرِسٌ","root":"Ers","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"One"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who quits not the place of conflict, by reason of courage."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEarisu","text_ar":"العَرِسُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The lion:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K:) because he keeps to the preying upon men; or because he keeps to his covert, or retreat. (O, * TA.)       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Confounded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perplexed, and unable to see his right course;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dahi$N","text_ar":"دَهِشٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, O, K.)"}],"source_refs":["O","K"]},{"entry_id":"n28647","headword_ar":"عُرُسٌ","root":"Ers","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EurosN","text_ar":"عُرْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}